riscv: dts: spacemit: k1-orangepi-rv2: constrain microSD to high-speed

Our tree backports only the SD pad-clock fix (patch 0002), not the K1
UHS voltage-switch/tuning driver commits (00a97fc57c09, e9cb83c10071).
Requesting UHS (sd-uhs-sdr*) without that support risks a failed 1.8V
switch during card init. Drop the UHS modes and add no-1-8-v so the
card runs reliably in 3.3V high-speed mode. Revisit once the UHS driver
commits are backported.

--- a/arch/riscv/boot/dts/spacemit/k1-orangepi-rv2.dts	2026-07-03 16:37:59.325335069 +0000
+++ b/arch/riscv/boot/dts/spacemit/k1-orangepi-rv2.dts	2026-07-03 16:37:59.334335155 +0000
@@ -379,8 +379,6 @@
 	cap-sd-highspeed;
 	vmmc-supply = <&buck4_3v3>;
 	vqmmc-supply = <&aldo1>;
-	sd-uhs-sdr25;
-	sd-uhs-sdr50;
-	sd-uhs-sdr104;
 	status = "okay";
+	no-1-8-v;
 };
